parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause loss of brake fluid, leading to brake failure, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake lines rusted and leaking
area next to brake lines not rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake master cylinder can cause loss of brake fluid, leading to brake failure, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
loud popping noise when applying brakes
vehicle moves with driver's foot on the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Rotor Warping and Premature Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warping and premature wear of brake rotors can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake rotors warped
excessive wear of brake rotors
brake pedal pulsates
steering wheel vibrates
vehicle vibrates violently when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ABS system can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Anti-lock light does not go out
odd noise comes from the left side of the engine compartment
brakes grab when coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transmission and clutch can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Transmission shudders
speed control failed
auto transmission shudders shifting
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncommanded transmission downshifts can cause unexpected slowing or loss of power, leading to hazardous situations, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Transmission downshifts without warning
often while driving at high speeds
causing the vehicle to slow down or lose power. The transmission may also shift into neutral or lower gears unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Loss of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or loss of gear can cause unexpected slowing or loss of power, leading to hazardous situations, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Transmission slips out of gear
causing the vehicle to slow down or lose power. The transmission may also hesitate or refuse to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure or replacement can cause significant inconvenience and expense, as well as potential safety risks if the failure occurs while driving.
symptoms: Transmission failure or replacement
often requiring multiple repairs or replacements. The transmission may exhibit symptoms such as slipping
hesitation
or refusal to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shutter or vibration can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, as well as potential safety risks if the vibration affects vehicle control.
symptoms: Transmission shutter or vibration
often accompanied by difficulty shifting or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs, and potentially leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The temperature gauge goes from cold to hot instantaneously
the engine overheats
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the coolant level drops
the engine makes a moaning noise
the idle raises
the vehicle wants to accelerate even without pressure to the accelerator.
